WEBVTT

00:00:01.815 --> 00:00:03.817
Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.

00:00:05.068 --> 00:00:07.195
People who have used these drugs

00:00:07.278 --> 00:00:10.824
are now estimated
to total two million in Japan.

00:00:11.324 --> 00:00:14.410
The number of people arrested
for drug-related offenses

00:00:14.994 --> 00:00:17.205
is as many as 14,000 yearly.

00:00:18.248 --> 00:00:20.959
What the hell did you do?

00:00:21.042 --> 00:00:22.377
No, I didn't--

00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:24.754
Hey! Drop the cheap act!

00:00:26.673 --> 00:00:28.466
Whose orders are you two following?

00:00:28.550 --> 00:00:29.968
Spit it out already.

00:00:32.679 --> 00:00:34.597
Why are you pissing in my office?

00:00:34.681 --> 00:00:36.599
You're getting the floor all filthy!

00:00:38.268 --> 00:00:41.020
I'm telling you
not to stain the damn floor!

00:00:55.076 --> 00:00:56.369
Don't move!

00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:58.246
Or he dies.

00:01:01.416 --> 00:01:03.877
What do we do with him?

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:05.378
Guess we have to kill him.

00:01:05.461 --> 00:01:07.839
But killing a narcotics agent…

00:01:07.922 --> 00:01:09.549
What other choice is there?

00:01:09.632 --> 00:01:10.508
Okay, sir.

00:01:16.097 --> 00:01:19.184
Would you please let me be an S for you?

00:01:19.267 --> 00:01:20.977
If you're really with the NCD,

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:23.813
you'll have mutual coworkers
with the other NCD guy.

00:01:24.564 --> 00:01:27.609
If their numbers
are in both of your phones,

00:01:27.692 --> 00:01:28.985
I'll trust you.

00:01:29.068 --> 00:01:32.363
However, if they aren't…

00:01:34.699 --> 00:01:35.867
it's over for you.

00:01:45.376 --> 00:01:46.336
Okay.

00:01:47.045 --> 00:01:48.713
Okay. Is that so?

00:01:48.796 --> 00:01:49.797
All right.

00:01:50.757 --> 00:01:53.384
Okay, got it.

00:01:56.221 --> 00:01:59.641
There were no overlaps
between the data in this guy's phone

00:01:59.724 --> 00:02:02.018
and the other NCD agent's phone.

00:02:02.101 --> 00:02:05.647
So they didn't have any
shared phone numbers in them?

00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:06.564
Yes.

00:02:07.232 --> 00:02:08.441
Hey!

00:02:08.524 --> 00:02:10.318
So you were lying after all!

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:13.446
If you're not with the NCD,
who exactly are you?

00:02:13.529 --> 00:02:14.489
I told you I'm--

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:16.574
I've had it!

00:02:16.658 --> 00:02:17.909
I'm tired of this.

00:02:18.618 --> 00:02:19.744
Let's just kill him.

00:02:19.827 --> 00:02:21.579
Please listen to me.

00:02:22.205 --> 00:02:24.040
Anything can happen in the field.

00:02:24.123 --> 00:02:27.126
Why would I have the numbers
of other agents in my phone?

00:02:27.210 --> 00:02:29.045
You just don't give up, do you?

00:02:29.128 --> 00:02:31.130
Then why did the other guy's phone

00:02:31.214 --> 00:02:34.717
have the phone number
of the NCD headquarters in it, huh?

00:02:34.801 --> 00:02:35.927
That's because…

00:02:37.136 --> 00:02:41.015
he's a regular agent,
while I'm an undercover agent.

00:02:41.557 --> 00:02:43.393
I knew my phone could be checked.

00:02:43.476 --> 00:02:44.769
Oh, shut up.

00:02:44.852 --> 00:02:49.107
Okay, for the sake of argument,
let's say you really were an NCD agent.

00:02:49.190 --> 00:02:51.818
Why the hell do I have
to let you leave alive?

00:02:51.901 --> 00:02:53.319
I already told you!

00:02:53.403 --> 00:02:56.364
I'll leak information
to the Saeki Family if you do.

00:02:56.447 --> 00:02:58.324
And I told you I can't trust that!

00:02:58.408 --> 00:03:01.577
How do I know you won't betray me
as soon as I let you leave?

00:03:01.661 --> 00:03:03.162
I won't! I promise!

00:03:03.246 --> 00:03:05.164
Like I would take your word for it!

00:03:05.248 --> 00:03:06.207
Trust me!

00:03:06.290 --> 00:03:08.459
-I'm telling you I can't!
-Please!

00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:15.425
Fine.

00:03:16.968 --> 00:03:21.389
If you want me to trust you,
prove it to me through your actions.

00:03:23.433 --> 00:03:24.392
What?

00:04:27.413 --> 00:04:28.539
Is he dead?

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:30.291
He's dead.

00:04:31.209 --> 00:04:32.585
Kurosaki…

00:04:41.844 --> 00:04:43.179
Matsubara?

00:04:43.262 --> 00:04:47.475
Being a dealer for him was part
of your undercover investigation?

00:04:49.936 --> 00:04:50.978
Yes.

00:04:53.439 --> 00:04:54.565
The NCD guy?

00:04:55.233 --> 00:04:57.568
We were about to deal with him.

00:04:57.652 --> 00:04:59.028
Uncover him.

00:04:59.112 --> 00:05:00.196
Yes, sir.

00:05:19.549 --> 00:05:20.550
You kill him.

00:05:21.551 --> 00:05:22.385
What?

00:05:22.468 --> 00:05:23.928
You want my trust?

00:05:24.011 --> 00:05:25.888
Kill him with your own hands.

00:05:25.972 --> 00:05:28.683
Then I'll know you won't betray me.

00:05:28.766 --> 00:05:32.186
Because you'll be a murderer yourself.

00:05:34.355 --> 00:05:35.565
Although…

00:05:38.192 --> 00:05:40.862
Is he even still alive?

00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:49.162
Still kicking, huh?
Sure you're not a junkie zombie too?

00:05:51.038 --> 00:05:52.707
Come on, kill him!

00:06:07.889 --> 00:06:10.099
You think you can take me out?

00:06:10.183 --> 00:06:11.809
Just try it!

00:06:13.895 --> 00:06:15.563
That hurts.

00:06:18.232 --> 00:06:20.610
I'll kill you before you kill me.

00:06:21.986 --> 00:06:23.321
Damn it.

00:06:24.655 --> 00:06:26.616
You asked for it.

00:06:30.161 --> 00:06:31.829
You're swinging too wide!

00:06:31.913 --> 00:06:34.123
Are you even trying to hit him?

00:06:34.624 --> 00:06:36.792
I won't go down easy.

00:06:36.876 --> 00:06:39.754
Shut up, you half-dead asshole!

00:06:43.925 --> 00:06:46.177
Die!

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:48.262
Let's go for Saeki when we can.

00:07:03.778 --> 00:07:06.197
I'll kill every one of you.

00:07:11.577 --> 00:07:13.246
What a tough bastard.

00:07:13.329 --> 00:07:14.413
Give it.

00:07:19.710 --> 00:07:21.045
Use it.

00:07:21.128 --> 00:07:22.171
What?

00:07:22.755 --> 00:07:24.257
Hurry up.

00:07:28.344 --> 00:07:30.471
Do as he says. Pick it up.

00:07:45.987 --> 00:07:46.946
My left abdomen.

00:07:47.029 --> 00:07:48.406
Stab it.

00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:51.033
What are you saying? If I do that--

00:07:51.117 --> 00:07:54.620
Just do it!
It's the only way you can live!

00:07:55.788 --> 00:07:56.747
Five.

00:07:57.248 --> 00:07:58.249
Four.

00:07:58.791 --> 00:07:59.792
Three.

00:08:00.293 --> 00:08:01.085
Two.

00:08:01.168 --> 00:08:02.128
I can't.

00:08:02.753 --> 00:08:04.213
I can't do it.

00:08:06.674 --> 00:08:07.633
One.

00:08:13.180 --> 00:08:14.557
Well, shit.

00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:17.310
-Shinichi, Shinji. Kill him.
-Yes, sir.

00:08:23.691 --> 00:08:24.650
Huh?

00:08:26.694 --> 00:08:29.071
Yes, that's good.

00:08:29.822 --> 00:08:30.906
You're--

00:08:31.699 --> 00:08:35.536
With this, you'll earn their trust.

00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:36.621
Why?

00:08:40.875 --> 00:08:42.209
So you do have it in you.

00:08:43.377 --> 00:08:44.629
Why do that…

00:08:44.712 --> 00:08:45.713
Shut up.

00:08:46.297 --> 00:08:47.673
Don't say any more.

00:08:48.758 --> 00:08:50.343
What, he's still alive?

00:08:50.426 --> 00:08:52.094
-Hey.
-Yes, sir.

00:08:57.892 --> 00:08:58.893
Fucking bastard!

00:09:00.519 --> 00:09:01.395
I knew it!

00:09:02.855 --> 00:09:03.856
Let's go!

00:09:09.820 --> 00:09:10.988
That asshole!

00:09:11.072 --> 00:09:12.615
Don't let them escape! Jump!

00:09:12.698 --> 00:09:13.658
From here?

00:09:13.741 --> 00:09:15.159
Just jump!

00:09:15.242 --> 00:09:16.744
No way!

00:09:16.827 --> 00:09:18.954
Go that way then! Fucking useless wimps!

00:09:19.914 --> 00:09:21.207
You all right?

00:09:23.459 --> 00:09:26.837
-I'm gonna fall!
-You go too!

00:09:26.921 --> 00:09:29.757
-Don't! Please!
-You jump too, come on!

00:09:39.183 --> 00:09:40.685
You shouldn't have done that.

00:09:40.768 --> 00:09:42.478
What else was I supposed to do?

00:09:42.561 --> 00:09:43.521
Leave me.

00:09:43.604 --> 00:09:44.563
What?

00:09:44.647 --> 00:09:48.192
The bleeding looks bad,
but the left abdomen has no vital organs.

00:09:48.275 --> 00:09:49.193
What?

00:09:49.276 --> 00:09:52.738
It was to make them trust you.
You're so damn useless.

00:09:52.822 --> 00:09:54.615
Then tell me that!

00:09:54.699 --> 00:09:56.283
Stop!

00:09:58.703 --> 00:10:00.204
You go ahead.

00:10:00.287 --> 00:10:01.497
I can't leave you.

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:03.708
Then they'll kill us both!

00:10:03.791 --> 00:10:06.168
Run away and call the NCD!

00:10:20.558 --> 00:10:21.684
Kurosaki.

00:10:33.279 --> 00:10:34.822
Too bad for you.

00:10:36.449 --> 00:10:38.033
Get up.

00:10:42.663 --> 00:10:43.748
Hey.

00:10:46.459 --> 00:10:49.128
Take them back up,
and let's finally end all this.

00:10:49.211 --> 00:10:50.129
Yes, sir.

00:10:50.212 --> 00:10:51.380
Stand up, asshole.

00:10:59.180 --> 00:11:01.724
You're such a useless S.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:05.311
You forced me into being an S.

00:11:05.394 --> 00:11:07.897
This is all your fault.

00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:09.064
Yes.

00:11:09.857 --> 00:11:14.069
But I promise you,
I'll get you out of this alive.

00:11:14.153 --> 00:11:15.654
Don't give up.

00:11:16.530 --> 00:11:19.116
I don't know, I think this is it.

00:11:23.370 --> 00:11:24.580
What the…

00:11:33.756 --> 00:11:35.382
Oh, man.

00:11:36.842 --> 00:11:40.387
Rough day for the NCD's Mad Dog, isn't it?

00:11:41.222 --> 00:11:42.890
Who the fuck are you?

00:11:44.225 --> 00:11:45.476
Katsuragi.

00:11:48.020 --> 00:11:49.355
The police.

00:11:53.108 --> 00:11:54.777
-Arrest them all.
-Yes, sir.

00:12:06.956 --> 00:12:09.208
-What's your problem?
-Don't resist.

00:12:11.669 --> 00:12:12.878
Damn punk.

00:12:14.296 --> 00:12:15.297
Start walking.

00:12:15.381 --> 00:12:16.799
Get off me!

00:12:27.768 --> 00:12:28.686
Fucker!

00:12:39.321 --> 00:12:40.364
Hey.

00:12:42.408 --> 00:12:43.242
Start walking.

00:12:43.325 --> 00:12:44.493
Hands off me.

00:12:45.869 --> 00:12:47.913
Too bad for you.

00:12:47.997 --> 00:12:50.124
This case belongs to the police.

00:12:52.251 --> 00:12:54.044
Police mutt.

00:13:00.259 --> 00:13:02.261
Ministry mutt.

00:13:04.763 --> 00:13:07.433
Hey, call an ambulance, quick.

00:13:07.516 --> 00:13:09.184
Keep it down.

00:13:09.268 --> 00:13:11.478
He won't die even if you kill him.

00:13:11.562 --> 00:13:13.272
-Hey.
-Yes, sir.

00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:16.400
Can you move?

00:13:28.704 --> 00:13:31.290
How long did you know
something was going on?

00:13:32.291 --> 00:13:35.419
Since you got kidnapped
from the bay parking lot.

00:13:35.919 --> 00:13:39.298
That suit has a wiretap
and a GPS tracker hidden in it.

00:13:42.009 --> 00:13:43.093
What are these?

00:13:43.177 --> 00:13:45.929
I want you to infiltrate the Saeki Family.

00:13:48.140 --> 00:13:50.142
So you knew everything.

00:13:51.226 --> 00:13:53.687
Then you knew what was happening inside.

00:13:53.771 --> 00:13:55.564
Why didn't you come sooner?

00:13:57.024 --> 00:13:59.401
To fatten the pigs before the slaughter.

00:14:00.027 --> 00:14:01.111
What did you say?

00:14:01.987 --> 00:14:03.906
This was the real end goal.

00:14:03.989 --> 00:14:06.158
That's why I waited until the last moment.

00:14:06.241 --> 00:14:09.370
And guess what?
Now, I can even get them for murder.

00:14:09.953 --> 00:14:12.498
Under the Organized Crime Punishment Act,

00:14:12.581 --> 00:14:15.876
we can now go arrest
the entire organization.

00:14:17.336 --> 00:14:19.254
Fuck that!

00:14:19.338 --> 00:14:21.590
What do you take people's lives for?

00:14:23.175 --> 00:14:28.639
While you were trying to rack up points,
we were about to get killed!

00:14:40.109 --> 00:14:41.568
Results mean everything.

00:14:42.236 --> 00:14:44.947
I don't care about the life
of a punk like you.

00:14:46.532 --> 00:14:47.700
But well,

00:14:47.783 --> 00:14:52.663
you did do a relatively
decent job as an S this time.

00:14:53.247 --> 00:14:56.375
Sure. How about I treat you
to some okonomiyaki?

00:15:03.882 --> 00:15:05.300
Damn you.

00:15:26.947 --> 00:15:28.240
Kurosaki!

00:15:31.326 --> 00:15:32.453
Where are we?

00:15:33.287 --> 00:15:35.581
That's not what matters right now.

00:15:35.664 --> 00:15:39.168
If you got treated any later,
you could've died of blood loss!

00:15:39.251 --> 00:15:41.628
Why do you always act so selfishly--

00:15:41.712 --> 00:15:42.838
What?

00:15:42.921 --> 00:15:45.215
Were we able to arrest them?

00:15:48.761 --> 00:15:50.095
Well…

00:15:51.180 --> 00:15:52.681
the police took them all.

00:16:00.939 --> 00:16:02.274
Kurosaki.

00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:05.736
Have some faith in us too for once.

00:16:14.161 --> 00:16:17.956
Their obsession with the junkies
made them blind to everything else.

00:16:19.416 --> 00:16:20.959
What incompetent fools.

00:16:22.586 --> 00:16:25.005
I'll let the higher-ups
know about this case.

00:16:26.173 --> 00:16:27.800
Thank you, sir.

00:16:27.883 --> 00:16:28.801
On that note,

00:16:29.343 --> 00:16:33.472
can we get the bigger smuggling ring
that the Saeki Family was working with?

00:16:35.474 --> 00:16:36.642
Well, about that…

00:16:38.477 --> 00:16:39.311
What is it?

00:16:40.854 --> 00:16:43.023
We searched the Saeki Family premises,

00:16:43.857 --> 00:16:47.402
but their computers had been wiped,
and we didn't find any USBs either.

00:16:49.738 --> 00:16:50.989
How did that happen?

00:16:51.865 --> 00:16:55.744
I believe they might have wiped it
as soon as the NCD got in there.

00:16:57.329 --> 00:16:58.163
No.

00:16:59.289 --> 00:17:01.625
They got into the office first,

00:17:03.335 --> 00:17:05.587
so the NCD might have done it.

00:17:06.171 --> 00:17:07.506
But that's…

00:17:08.841 --> 00:17:11.051
The agent's name was Kurosaki, wasn't it?

00:17:12.177 --> 00:17:14.263
He's got a pretty keen nose.

00:17:14.847 --> 00:17:17.641
He's always wherever the drugs are.

00:17:18.433 --> 00:17:19.977
Keep track of him,

00:17:20.644 --> 00:17:24.481
and beat the NCD to the punch
on every single case from now on.

00:17:24.982 --> 00:17:25.858
Yes, sir.

00:17:28.819 --> 00:17:30.154
Know this, Katsuragi.

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:35.200
It's the police that protect
this country from threats,

00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:37.452
not the NCD.

00:17:38.662 --> 00:17:40.038
Don't forget that.

00:17:41.373 --> 00:17:42.416
Yes, sir.

00:18:03.937 --> 00:18:05.772
You look terrible.

00:18:07.566 --> 00:18:09.776
Hey, you listening?

00:18:11.361 --> 00:18:14.615
Get out, you useless S.

00:18:16.617 --> 00:18:18.577
Who's useless again?

00:18:24.124 --> 00:18:25.209
And that is?

00:18:27.920 --> 00:18:29.171
COPYING FOUR ITEMS

00:18:33.258 --> 00:18:34.259
Hello, sir!

00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:36.386
Where's Shinichi and Shinji?

00:18:41.433 --> 00:18:42.434
Here.

00:18:45.187 --> 00:18:48.398
It has info on not just
the underlying organization,

00:18:48.482 --> 00:18:51.401
but also the client list,
their smuggling routes,

00:18:51.485 --> 00:18:53.695
and their past transactions too.

00:18:58.575 --> 00:18:59.534
You…

00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:04.373
I wouldn't say no to a compliment.

00:19:08.835 --> 00:19:10.254
You did great.

00:19:12.589 --> 00:19:15.926
Wait, I didn't think
you would actually compliment me.

00:19:19.179 --> 00:19:20.472
You did great.

00:19:24.977 --> 00:19:27.312
Hey, knock it off.

00:19:39.241 --> 00:19:40.951
Man, it hurts.

00:19:44.997 --> 00:19:48.792
Ryu Saeki, the leader of the Saeki Family,

00:19:48.875 --> 00:19:52.170
a drug smuggling organization
and organized crime group,

00:19:52.254 --> 00:19:55.090
was found dead in his jail cell.

00:19:55.924 --> 00:19:59.303
The police are investigating it
as a potential suicide.

00:20:00.012 --> 00:20:05.225
The Narcotics Control Department
is also investigating the case,

00:20:05.309 --> 00:20:08.854
expecting a larger smuggling ring
to be behind the Saeki Family.

00:20:09.354 --> 00:20:10.731
The police also say

00:20:10.814 --> 00:20:17.821
that several persons of interest related
to this case have reportedly gone missing.

00:20:17.904 --> 00:20:21.783
There may be more to come
in regards to this drug smuggling case.

00:20:22.576 --> 00:20:24.411
On to our next news,

00:20:25.454 --> 00:20:30.334
there was a fire today in Kokuryocho,
Chofu City, at the Marsan Apartments.

00:20:30.417 --> 00:20:33.378
MOTHER AND DAUGHTER
IN CRITICAL CONDITION AFTER FIRE

00:23:04.654 --> 00:23:05.780
The usual.

00:23:28.887 --> 00:23:30.096
Let's go.

00:23:37.771 --> 00:23:40.607
What should we have for dinner?

00:23:40.690 --> 00:23:46.071
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

00:23:46.154 --> 00:23:47.113
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan